description: Cap City Collective partnered with COMBO to put on a test event last summer at Chestnut Ridge MTB trails in order to appeal to a wider range of riders. Columbus Cyclocross Practice Series
description:
Join Cap City Collective and the Columbus cyclocross community for another year of cyclocross practices! This year the practices will remain at Cap City Collective's home base, Big Run Park's Derby Hill. This practice is appropriate for riders of all levels, from "I've never ridden a bike on the dirt before" to "I podium at Cincy2."

    Helmets and a functional bike (Cyclocross or MTB) are required.
    Water & food are not available on site, so please come prepared.
    Gloves and glasses are recommended.

The venue will be open from 5pm until dark, with organized instruction beginning at 6pm. The series runs every Tuesday evening starting the second Tuesday in August until the last Tuesday in October.
notes:
Tentative Practice schedule:

    Week 1 - Barriers & Introduction to Cyclocross
    Week 2 - Cornering & Starts
    Week 3 - Climbing & Off Cambers
    Week 4-13 - will begin the mock races.
        We will have a short course arranged with flags or tape to simulate situations you will encounter in real races.
        A, B, & C groups will each have 2-3 chances to race throughout the night.
        New or inexperienced riders will be able to participate in breakout sessions to work on specific skills independent of the racing.

About The Donations & Cost

In the past cyclocross practices in Columbus have been free. These practices were uninsured and not permitted. To use Big Run Park and to take advantage of the insurance provided by USA Cycling Cap City Collective is required to cover the fees associated with the USA Cycling Permit, the City of Columbus park permit, and a per-rider insurance fee. Your donations will go directly to covering these costs. Any profits will be directly contributed to future off-road development programming through Cap City Collective. A $55 donation will cover the per-rider insurance fees for one rider and a portion of the permitting fees for the event. You are encouraged to donate more than $55 to cover other riders or future programming.
directions:
Big Run Park - Derby Hill
4201 Clime Rd,
Columbus, OH 43228

title: Mayhem MTB Festival - Short Track
description:
Paradise Garage Short Track Event

Saturday, October 7th

Short Track is a .5-1.5 mile loop of Olympic style XC MTB racing. The course will have typical features you would encounter on trail, but in rapid fire succession (every 20-30 seconds). This format of racing is very spectator friendly and will be almost entirely man-made.
course: This short track race will embody the spirit of the mayhem and will have A-lines with jumps, drops, berms, etc.. and B-lines (ride arounds) for those who are less daring. This type of racing not only pits the competitor against the course, but also against a field of multiple racers. Races are mass start by starting time and skill level.
notes: Pre-ride is mandatory and will open at 9:00 am Saturday, October 7th. Registration will close 15 minutes prior to each race. Day of registration and one-day licenses will be available on-site.

Cap City Cross #6 - Paradise Garage Racing @ Big Run Park
description:
Fast, rolling terrain with off cambers, paved, the monstrous derby hill, grass climbing, and wide open turns.

This year we are planning on bringing back some of the classic features (the derby hill start, treacherous off cambers and fast flow to reward your climbing efforts), but we will also add some brand new features that have never been seen before.

Presented by Paradise Garage Racing
course:
Fast, rolling terrain with off cambers, paved, the monstrous derby hill, grass climbing, and wide open turns.

This year we are planning on bringing back some of the classic features (the derby hill start, treacherous off cambers and fast flow to reward your climbing efforts), but we will also add some brand new features that have never been seen before.
notes:
Note: We can only accept credit card on site. No cash or check will be accepted for day of registration per City of Columbus rules.

Race more!
After registering for one race the cost of each additional race on the same day is only $10.00. This discount will be automatically applied when registering for multiple races. 

Callups:

    We will be doing call-ups based on CrossResults.com points for ALL pre-registered riders. Day of registered riders will be staged in order of registration. Pre-register for you best call-up!

Kids Race: 

The kid's race is FREE, sweets, treats and more for all that enter! Kids will have a separate, smaller circuit course located near the start/finish. The kids race will begin at 1:30, but the kid's course will be open all day for riding. 

Numbers & Fine Print

All results will be submitted to USAC within 48 hours after the official results are final.

The promoter and / or officials reserve the right to lengthen, shorten, modify, combine or cancel races and or prize list as a result of insufficient entries, inclement weather, dangerous conditions, statutes and laws, emergencies, and or race conditions.

Race day registration begins at 8:30am and closes approximately 15 minutes before each race

    This race is held under USA Cycling rules.  All racers must have a valid USAC license.
    One day USAC licenses (Men Cat 5 & Women Cat 4 only, One-day licenses may also be used for "Open" category races like Masters and SS if you are Men Category 5 or Women Category 4 - all other categories in the "Open" race will be required to have an annual USAC license) will be available for $10.00.
directions: Derby Hill - Big Run Park - 4201 Clime Rd, Columbus, OH  43228
